								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Analysis:</i> This acquisition is for end products for use in the United States and is set aside for small business concerns. The Buy American statute applies. Since the acquisition value is less than $25,000 and the acquisition is set aside, none of the trade agreements apply. Perform the steps in <xref href="FAR-i1091565.dita#i1091565"
                              base="i1091565"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.502</xref>(a). Offer C is evaluated as a foreign end product because it is the product of a small business, but is not a domestic end product (see <xref href="FAR-i1091565.dita#i1091565"
                              base="i1091565"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.502</xref>(c)(4)). Since Offer B is a domestic offer, apply the 12 percent factor to Offer C (see <xref href="FAR-i1093701.dita#i1093701"
                              base="i1093701"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.105</xref>(b)(2)). The resulting evaluated price of $11,200 remains lower than Offer B. The cost of Offer B is therefore unreasonable (see <xref href="FAR-i1093701.dita#i1093701"
                              base="i1093701"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.105</xref>(c)). Award on Offer C at $10,000 (see <xref href="FAR-i1091565.dita#i1091565"
                              base="i1091565"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25.502</xref>(c)(4)(i)).</p>
